<item>
            <title>[TIKA-497] HtmlHandler should fix up incorrect capitalization of names in &lt;meta http-equiv=&quot;xxx&quot;&gt; attributes before putting into metadata</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-497</link>
                <project id="12310631" key="TIKA">Tika</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;With the current behavior, you can get metadata entries that have &quot;Content-Type&quot; and &quot;content-type&quot; as their names, because http-equiv attribute values often use incorrect capitalization.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12472477">TIKA-497</key>
            <summary>HtmlHandler should fix up incorrect capitalization of names in &lt;meta http-equiv=&quot;xxx&quot;&gt; attributes before putting into metadata</summary>
