                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12902457" author="jukkaz" created="Wed, 25 Aug 2010 15:19:03 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Instead of just fixing the capitalization, I&apos;d argue that the HTML parser should specifically look for these kinds of well known metadata keys and automatically map such information to the applicable Metadata constants we already have. If there are multiple sources for a particular metadata entry (Content-Type is a perfect example), then reasonable heuristics should be used to merge the information.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12926829" author="chrismattmann" created="Mon, 1 Nov 2010 05:24:29 +0000"  >&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;pushing out to 0.9 &amp;#8211; there&apos;s no patch for this yet and it&apos;s 0.8 release time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12929420" author="chrismattmann" created="Mon, 8 Nov 2010 00:41:04 +0000"  >&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;classify&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12993063" author="jukkaz" created="Thu, 10 Feb 2011 14:21:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I added a very simple version of metadata normalization in revision 1069400. It might be a good idea to generalize that into something like a MetadataNormalizer class in tika-core, so it would be easier to test, reuse and extend.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
